	<Body>
		<Section>
			<SectionHead />
			<HTML>
				&lt;p&gt;
Very few people who have low back pain require surgery of any kind to obtain relief from their discomfort. But if conservative treatments haven&apos;t resolved your pain within six months and your doctor has determined that your disk joint is the source of your chronic pain, you might be a candidate for disk replacement surgery.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Spinal fusion &amp;mdash; the most common type of back surgery for painful joints &amp;mdash; involves fusing two or more vertebrae together. Disk replacement surgery is a newer procedure that replaces the problem disk joint with an artificial one made of metal and plastic.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
In general, it appears that spinal fusion and disk replacement procedures are equally effective. But in some cases, intensive rehabilitation programs appear to work just as well as either type of surgery &amp;mdash; at a lower cost and with fewer complications.
&lt;/p&gt;
			</HTML>
		</Section>
	</Body>
	<Title>
		Disk replacement: An effective treatment for low back pain?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Disk replacement is a relatively new treatment option for degenerative disk disease.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		Is disk replacement surgery an effective treatment for low back pain?
	</Question>
